I've only been playing the game since August this year, and I don't know enough of the game (areas/zones/loot/pp/exp) to be a good guildleader...<br>
<br>
I am fine being an officer, as it is, helping out our new members along the way.  I've got a lot of people in my guild liking me for the help I've given them.<br>
<br>
As for interacting with others - I'm a sociable, easy to get along with type of person - but to start serious bonding with other players/guilds in-game - there's the problem of me being one of the not so big a group of players representing the continent of Europe...<br>
And then to be a leader and forging these bonds, strengthening them, ...  I fear I lack the nighttime to play.<br>
<br>
I don't find many people on-line at my playing times as opposed to weekends, when there's nighttime for me to play in and I see hundreds instead of a few handfuls.<br>
<br>
I can maybe list two handfuls of people I regularly play with - and that's because they have the same playing times as me, though not all being European (nighshift working people in US/Australia and Canada as well as a few local friends from Belgium).<br>
<br>
Also, the problem with our guildleader MIA makes it tough for us to make new officers... as it is, there's currently only two 'active' officers left - me and Dukvodju Runecake...    Two other GAG'ers have already been appointed to become officers - Tokeymi our Dark Ambassador and Kappelheimer our Master of Materials - but they can not be given leadership due to our leader being missing.<br>
<br>
As for leading a guild - maybe in a few months, when I've more knowledge of the game, maybe even know some stuff about other classes, to be useful.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the vote of confidence though Baldisking - it is appreciated ;-)  I am doing fine being a Mage, I think I have the knack of being one (I was born for it? :-p ), and from what people have told me, I'm a proficient one (knowing what to do with two mobs, helping my pet taunt adds off a tank, knowing when to nuke and when not to...).  I have saved many a life in doing so...    Sure, I may have killed some people accidentally with a bad pull, or dying before they could zone and being trapped by a mob, but then I have always offered those my sincerest apologies and a res in case they accepted one and a Cleric or Pally was about.<br>
<br>
So, we're planning (we - me and Dukvodju) to wait until Thanksgiving for our guildleader to show up, before petitioning a GM for transfer of leadership - to Dukvodju, since he has been playing EQ on and off over the last few years, and has been organising raids and events lately, which were always fun.<br>
<br>
So, as for me being a guildleader - maybe when I grow up in game.  As for me wanting to team up with any and all - I'll give anyone a chance ;-)<br>
/OOC<br>
